<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13497] Remove MVCC stamps from HFile when that is safe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13497</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See discussion in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13389&quot; title=&quot;[REGRESSION] HBASE-12600 undoes skip-mvcc parse optimizations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-13389&quot;&gt;HBASE-13389&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
The optimization was initially put in with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8166&quot; title=&quot;Avoid writing the memstoreTS into HFiles when possible&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8166&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-8166&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12600&quot; title=&quot;Remove REPLAY tag dependency in Distributed Replay Mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12600&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-12600&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; undoes it, this will partially restores it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead of checking the MVCC readpoints against the oldest current scanner, we check that all are 0, if so, we do not need to write them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
